CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 2, 1958, pg. A12, reads: "The FROGS Have Fun - Frog Week opened last Sunday with a gay party for members, their wives and out-of-town guests at the Terrain Room of Terrace Hall.  The above pictures tell the story of how the Frogs and their guests had fun...  The last photo show, in the foreground, Dr. Melvin Stockton, chairman of the Sunday affair, with Mrs. J. D. Primas (back to camera), Mrs. Stockton, Dr. John Woodyear and Dr. J. D. Primas. - All Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Dr. William Melvin Stockton, Mrs. Primas (back to camera), Mrs. Stockton, Dr. John Woodyear, and Dr. J. D. Primas gathered around table, at FROGS week party in Terrain Room of Terrace Hall
